President Muhammadu Buhari has proclaimed that the first session of the 9th National Assembly members will hold on Tuesday, 11 June 2019 by 10am in the two Chambers. This is in line with session 64 (3) where the person elected as president shall issue a proclamation for the holding of the first session of the National Assembly immediately after being sworn-in. In keeping faith with the rule of law, President Buhari issued the proclamation in a statement he personally signed dated 30th May, 2019. The statement said: “Whereas it is provided in section 64(3) of the Constitution of the Federal Republic of Nigeria 1999 (as amended) that the  person elected as president shall have power to issue a proclamation for the holding of the first session of the holding of the first session of the National Assembly immediately after being sworn-in. Now, therefore, I, Muhammadu Buhari, President and Commander-in-Chief of the Armed Forces of the Federal Republic of Nigeria, in exercise of the powers bestowed upon me by Session 54(3) aforesaid, and of all other powers enabling me in that behalf, hereby proclaim that the first session of the ninth National Assembly shall hold at 10:00am on Tuesday, 11 June, 2019 in the National Assembly, Abuja. “Given under my hand and the public seal of the Federal Republic of Nigeria at Abuja, this 30th May, 2019.”